WEBVTT

00:06.173 --> 00:09.176
<i>[pensive instrumental music]</i>

00:09.176 --> 00:16.183
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:23.065 --> 00:26.110
<i>[woman singing in Norwegian]</i>

00:26.110 --> 00:33.117
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:45.796 --> 00:52.803
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:21.749 --> 01:24.126
Careful, it's powerful stuff.

01:24.126 --> 01:25.336
You sure that remote
even work, <i>ke?</i>

01:25.336 --> 01:27.087
I wired it myself.

01:27.087 --> 01:28.547
It will work.

01:32.218 --> 01:34.261
[distant roar]

01:34.261 --> 01:37.264
<i>[ominous music]</i>

01:37.264 --> 01:38.182
[Lucia] They're here,

01:38.182 --> 01:39.350
ten hours early!

01:40.726 --> 01:42.019
No, leave <i>im!</i>

01:42.019 --> 01:43.103
We have to remove
the charge.

01:43.103 --> 01:44.188
Their drive will set it off.

01:44.188 --> 01:45.147
Then it does.

01:45.147 --> 01:46.273
At least blow it now,

01:46.273 --> 01:47.399
before they land.

01:47.399 --> 01:48.567
Give them a chance to pull up.

01:48.567 --> 01:50.569
Nah.
Fuck <i>Inyalowda.</i>

01:50.569 --> 01:52.112
This isn't
what we planned.

01:52.112 --> 01:54.114
I did not come here
to kill people.

01:54.114 --> 01:55.991
The plan is what I say it is.

01:55.991 --> 01:57.827
Whatever happen, their fault.

01:59.370 --> 02:00.996
[huffs]

02:00.996 --> 02:02.039
[Coop] No!

02:04.124 --> 02:11.131
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:14.134 --> 02:17.429
[laughs]
Big surprise for landing, eh?

02:17.429 --> 02:19.223
They got it coming, them.

02:19.223 --> 02:20.724
[Scotty] Yeah.

02:20.724 --> 02:27.731
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:27.731 --> 02:29.441
[Coop] Lucia, no!

02:29.441 --> 02:33.487
[panting]

02:33.487 --> 02:36.031
There, there.
You're safe now.

02:37.783 --> 02:39.618
What happened?

02:39.618 --> 02:42.288
Oh, auto-doc
just knocked you out

02:42.288 --> 02:44.874
while I was packing
your wounds.

02:44.874 --> 02:46.333
[sighs]

02:46.333 --> 02:47.751
Go easy.

02:47.751 --> 02:49.086
We're on the float.

02:50.087 --> 02:51.630
[Alex] You got some
deep tissue damage.

02:51.630 --> 02:52.923
That's the kind of thing
that doesn't do

02:52.923 --> 02:55.718
too well in zero-G, so...

02:55.718 --> 02:57.761
I guess this means
we made it.

02:57.761 --> 02:59.388
[chuckles]

02:59.388 --> 03:00.848
Welcome to the <i>Rocinante.</i>

03:01.765 --> 03:03.434
[Alex laughs]

03:06.520 --> 03:08.063
You okay?

03:09.523 --> 03:10.691
I'll be fine.

03:12.568 --> 03:14.612
<i>[pensive music]</i>

03:14.612 --> 03:16.030
My family...

03:16.030 --> 03:17.489
Murtry said...

03:17.489 --> 03:19.241
We haven't heard anything yet.

03:20.034 --> 03:21.285
But Holden will
take care of it.

03:21.285 --> 03:22.828
[Alex] That's right.

03:22.828 --> 03:23.996
Holden's not gonna let
anything happen to them,

03:23.996 --> 03:24.997
I promise.

03:24.997 --> 03:30.210
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:37.593 --> 03:40.262
[Mason] Yeah, then there was
this place on Titan.

03:40.262 --> 03:42.097
Yeah, I used to go there
when I was in training.

03:42.097 --> 03:44.642
They had this grilled corn
with garlic butter, you know?

03:44.642 --> 03:47.144
- I do not.
- Yeah, garlic butter,

03:47.144 --> 03:49.647
and they had these sides,
these green sides.

03:49.647 --> 03:51.607
I don't know what they were.
They kind of looked...

03:51.607 --> 03:52.858
Wait outside
until you're relieved.

03:52.858 --> 03:54.360
I'll watch this one.

04:00.115 --> 04:02.910
That guy talks a lot.

04:02.910 --> 04:04.912
Mason's an idiot.

04:06.372 --> 04:07.915
Lot of those on your team.

04:09.750 --> 04:12.044
You know,
in a different context,

04:12.044 --> 04:13.712
this could be kind of fun.

04:14.546 --> 04:15.881
Come on.

04:15.881 --> 04:17.257
Don't be mad.

04:19.051 --> 04:21.470
Trade places with me,
and then we'll talk about it.

04:21.470 --> 04:23.222
Don't be an asshole.
I saved your life out there.

04:23.222 --> 04:24.848
- Maybe.
- Oh, really?

04:24.848 --> 04:25.849
You think you could take on

04:25.849 --> 04:27.184
all my men by yourself?

04:27.184 --> 04:28.686
I had a shot.

04:31.188 --> 04:33.691
You are so fucking weird.

04:34.817 --> 04:35.818
<i>[Holden] Amos!</i>

04:35.818 --> 04:37.277
In here!

04:37.277 --> 04:38.445
Shit.

04:39.405 --> 04:42.408
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

04:42.408 --> 04:49.415
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:51.208 --> 04:52.960
- [metallic clanging]
- [woman shushing]

04:52.960 --> 04:54.878
[indistinct whispering]

04:54.878 --> 04:58.340
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:58.340 --> 05:00.134
[woman quavers]

05:00.134 --> 05:05.931
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:05.931 --> 05:07.558
Amos!

05:08.892 --> 05:10.686
Settlement's in lockdown.

05:10.686 --> 05:13.147
No one outside their quarters
unless Chief Murtry says so.

05:13.147 --> 05:14.690
I don't give a fuck
what Murtry said.

05:14.690 --> 05:15.899
Where's my crewman?

05:18.193 --> 05:20.154
Module seven.

05:22.114 --> 05:24.742
- [device beeps]
- Sir, we have a situation.

05:24.742 --> 05:26.744
<i>[Murtry] I'm well aware.</i>
- [device beeps]

05:27.745 --> 05:33.250
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:33.250 --> 05:35.044
Unlock him.

05:35.044 --> 05:36.795
Not gonna happen.
Put the gun down.

05:36.795 --> 05:38.297
[Amos] Don't kill her.

05:38.297 --> 05:40.007
She just hasn't figured out
her boss is a dick.

05:40.007 --> 05:41.592
- You stay out of it.
[Amos] Hey.

05:41.592 --> 05:43.761
Give me the key and walk away.

05:43.761 --> 05:45.804
There's no need
to die over this shit.

05:47.931 --> 05:49.892
Fuck that.

05:49.892 --> 05:51.393
[Murtry] Captain Holden.

05:51.393 --> 05:52.644
You left

05:52.644 --> 05:54.313
before we could finish
our talk.

05:54.313 --> 05:55.981
Cut him loose.
Do it now.

05:55.981 --> 05:57.441
We don't have time
for your vendetta.

05:57.441 --> 05:58.901
Vendetta?

05:58.901 --> 06:01.111
The artifacts on this planet
are waking up.

06:01.111 --> 06:03.238
The device my ship just blew up
would've wiped

06:03.238 --> 06:04.740
this settlement off the map.

06:04.740 --> 06:06.366
We need to get everyone
off the surface

06:06.366 --> 06:08.118
before something even worse
shows up.

06:08.118 --> 06:09.578
You're saying we need
to evacuate?

06:09.578 --> 06:11.497
Yes, immediately.

06:15.125 --> 06:15.959
Unlock him.

06:18.087 --> 06:19.296
Don't think I've forgotten

06:19.296 --> 06:20.839
that you're sheltering
a murderer,

06:20.839 --> 06:23.258
but if you intend to evacuate
everyone into orbit,

06:23.258 --> 06:25.969
then RCE will do whatever
it can to aid your effort.

06:25.969 --> 06:28.305
This isn't about your claim
on the planet anymore.

06:28.305 --> 06:29.807
I understand.

06:29.807 --> 06:32.267
You wanna keep your people
safe, and so do I.

06:32.267 --> 06:34.061
[Amos] He'll only help
as long as evacuating

06:34.061 --> 06:35.979
the Belters is easier
than shooting them.

06:35.979 --> 06:37.481
- I know.
[Murtry] You people act

06:37.481 --> 06:39.691
like I'm the bad guy here.

06:39.691 --> 06:41.318
I came on a peaceful mission.

06:41.318 --> 06:42.986
These squatters
drew first blood.

06:42.986 --> 06:44.738
And you used it
to justify murder.

06:44.738 --> 06:47.282
I acted against terrorists
who killed innocent people

06:47.282 --> 06:48.992
and were planning
further acts of violence,

06:48.992 --> 06:50.285
but I'm the bad guy.

06:50.285 --> 06:51.328
You and your friend here

06:51.328 --> 06:52.871
assault me and my people,

06:52.871 --> 06:54.248
but I'm the bad guy.

06:54.248 --> 06:56.500
Maybe I've just got
that kind of face.

06:56.500 --> 06:58.085
I'll make sure

06:58.085 --> 07:00.504
you get to tell your story
in court...

07:00.504 --> 07:01.964
at a murder trial.

07:01.964 --> 07:03.757
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

07:03.757 --> 07:05.592
One way or another,
we all answer

07:05.592 --> 07:07.261
for what we've done.

07:07.261 --> 07:10.556
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:10.556 --> 07:13.016
[Murtry] Tell everyone to pack.
[Wei] Are we really leaving?

07:13.016 --> 07:16.311
Well, only
if the Belters leave too.

07:16.311 --> 07:18.355
Get everyone round up.

07:18.355 --> 07:20.274
This evacuation is real,
but you and I better be

07:20.274 --> 07:21.567
the last two people
on those shuttles.

07:21.567 --> 07:23.110
Understood.

07:23.110 --> 07:26.572
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:26.572 --> 07:28.157
[device beeps]

07:28.157 --> 07:29.199
<i>[man] This is
the</i> Edward Israel.

07:29.199 --> 07:30.576
<i>Go ahead, sir.</i>

07:30.576 --> 07:32.661
Both light shuttles
in working order?

07:32.661 --> 07:34.079
<i>[man] Yes, sir.</i>

07:34.079 --> 07:36.415
Take the secondary one,

07:36.415 --> 07:37.666
disable the safeties,

07:37.666 --> 07:39.751
rig it up for remote piloting,

07:39.751 --> 07:42.296
and put it
on a proximity trigger.

07:42.296 --> 07:45.215
<i>[man] You want me to make it
into a bomb?</i>

07:45.215 --> 07:48.677
I want you to make it
into an option.

07:48.677 --> 07:49.511
[device beeps]

07:50.846 --> 07:53.098
Have the Belters broadcast
any of these images?

07:53.098 --> 07:54.808
No, ma'am, RCE said

07:54.808 --> 07:57.686
the <i>Edward Israel</i>
was the only ship recording it.

07:57.686 --> 07:59.730
Good.
I want these kept under wraps.

07:59.730 --> 08:02.149
The last thing I need
is terror in the streets.

08:02.149 --> 08:03.609
Understood.

08:03.609 --> 08:04.985
Let's get this over with.

08:04.985 --> 08:06.737
[Arjun] Look at me
like I'm the camera.

08:06.737 --> 08:08.447
Treat the lens like a friend,

08:08.447 --> 08:10.240
and everyone on the other side
of the screen

08:10.240 --> 08:11.992
will feel it.

08:11.992 --> 08:13.702
[aide] Madam Secretary,

08:13.702 --> 08:15.579
why did you approve
the higher grain allotments

08:15.579 --> 08:17.748
for the European
Shared Interest Zone?

08:17.748 --> 08:19.541
The grain allotments
haven't been adjusted...

08:19.541 --> 08:20.667
Relax your shoulders.

08:20.667 --> 08:22.252
Just talk to me.

08:24.880 --> 08:27.382
The grain allotments
haven't been adjusted

08:27.382 --> 08:29.343
for almost 15 years.

08:29.343 --> 08:31.720
In that time,
immigration between zones...

08:31.720 --> 08:32.888
Use simpler diction.

08:32.888 --> 08:35.682
Just say "people moving"
instead.

08:36.808 --> 08:39.519
This is a waste of my time.

08:42.606 --> 08:45.359
Who the fuck cares
about any of this?

08:45.359 --> 08:48.362
Food allotment will be
a key campaign issue.

08:48.362 --> 08:51.406
James Holden
and a bunch of Belters

08:51.406 --> 08:54.368
are fucking up
our first exploration

08:54.368 --> 08:56.495
of an alien world,

08:56.495 --> 08:59.289
but yes, let's talk
about the grain shipments.

08:59.289 --> 09:01.041
No matter where
the debate leads,

09:01.041 --> 09:04.002
we need you to come off
as more approachable,

09:04.002 --> 09:05.212
nurturing,

09:05.212 --> 09:06.588
the caring family matriarch.

09:06.588 --> 09:08.006
- It tested...
- Get the fuck out.

09:14.930 --> 09:16.306
Hmm.

09:18.058 --> 09:20.602
They're trying to help.

09:20.602 --> 09:23.730
Caring matriarch?

09:23.730 --> 09:25.524
It's an election debate.

09:25.524 --> 09:27.484
They just want you
to play the game.

09:28.860 --> 09:30.195
Fuck.

09:30.195 --> 09:33.198
You and that RCE
security woman.

09:34.199 --> 09:35.284
- Wei?
- Yeah.

09:35.284 --> 09:37.369
Is she gonna be a problem?

09:37.369 --> 09:39.329
- For who?
- Where is my family?

09:39.329 --> 09:40.747
Do you know what happened
to them?

09:40.747 --> 09:42.791
Lucia's on my ship,
and my ship is in orbit.

09:42.791 --> 09:44.376
- She's safe.
- And Felcia?

09:44.376 --> 09:45.919
Was my daughter with her?

09:45.919 --> 09:47.546
I'm sorry.
I haven't seen her.

09:51.842 --> 09:53.677
[Amos] Excuse me.

09:55.804 --> 09:56.888
- We need to talk.
- We're not leaving.

09:56.888 --> 09:57.973
You don't understand.

09:57.973 --> 09:59.891
There was a massive machine

09:59.891 --> 10:01.768
in the desert
that would've leveled the town.

10:01.768 --> 10:03.979
We know.
The RCE scientist told us.

10:03.979 --> 10:06.315
And now the Inners
are going back to orbit.

10:06.315 --> 10:08.150
Fine, let them.

10:08.150 --> 10:10.569
This settlement and everyone
in it would be dead.

10:10.569 --> 10:12.487
You're not, only because
a torpedo from my ship

10:12.487 --> 10:13.822
was able to kill it,

10:13.822 --> 10:15.115
but the next thing
could be a lot worse,

10:15.115 --> 10:16.575
and there will be
a next thing.

10:16.575 --> 10:17.993
You have no way
of knowing that.

10:17.993 --> 10:19.619
He actually does.

10:19.619 --> 10:22.372
We need to get everyone
off the planet right now.

10:23.457 --> 10:25.542
Was this RCE's plan
all along?

10:26.585 --> 10:28.003
No.
It was mine.

10:28.003 --> 10:29.421
Don't make this a fight.

10:29.421 --> 10:31.423
I don't know
if you're using Murtry

10:31.423 --> 10:33.592
or he's using you,

10:33.592 --> 10:36.845
but if we leave,
they'll never let us come back.

10:36.845 --> 10:38.889
You go if you want to.

10:38.889 --> 10:42.184
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

10:42.184 --> 10:45.187
[indistinct chatter]

10:49.232 --> 10:52.486
<i>[Fayez] The islands where all
that weird lightning ended up?</i>

10:52.486 --> 10:55.238
<i>They've started putting off
heat like a supervolcano...</i>

10:55.238 --> 10:57.199
<i>on a planet with no volcanoes.</i>

10:58.784 --> 11:00.577
[device beeps]

11:01.870 --> 11:03.288
What do you think it is?

11:03.288 --> 11:04.664
<i>More weird alien shit.</i>

11:05.749 --> 11:08.502
[sighs]

11:08.502 --> 11:10.504
This is a lot.

11:10.504 --> 11:11.755
I mean, I was expecting a lot,

11:11.755 --> 11:14.007
but this is a lot, a lot.

11:14.007 --> 11:15.467
<i>[Fayez] Right?</i>

11:16.843 --> 11:18.220
Does it seem strange to you

11:18.220 --> 11:19.805
<i>that these things have lasted</i>

11:19.805 --> 11:21.681
<i>millions, maybe billions,
of years</i>

11:21.681 --> 11:24.476
<i>and we can break them
with torpedoes?</i>

11:24.476 --> 11:26.269
Maybe they wore out
and got brittle.

11:26.269 --> 11:28.438
I had a, uh...
a refrigerator in college

11:28.438 --> 11:30.273
I left off over holiday,

11:30.273 --> 11:32.859
and when I turned it back on,
it caught fire.

11:32.859 --> 11:34.277
[chuckles softly]

11:35.070 --> 11:37.197
- Murtry wants you.
- Gotta go.

11:37.197 --> 11:38.573
<i>Wait.</i>

11:38.573 --> 11:40.200
- [device beeps]
- She's in here, sir.

11:40.200 --> 11:41.910
[device beeps]

11:41.910 --> 11:43.787
You might want to get that
checked out.

11:43.787 --> 11:47.457
Squatter camp hygiene makes
all sorts of nasty infections.

11:47.457 --> 11:50.502
- Just itches.
[Murtry] Dr. Okoye.

11:50.502 --> 11:54.214
I understand you saw the thing
that Holden destroyed.

11:54.214 --> 11:55.757
I did.
I told him not to.

11:55.757 --> 11:57.259
It's fine.

11:57.259 --> 11:59.803
I want to hear
about this alien technology.

12:00.929 --> 12:02.973
Every detail.

12:14.151 --> 12:17.154
<i>[pensive music]</i>

12:17.154 --> 12:24.161
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:29.624 --> 12:31.751
[computers beeping]

12:31.751 --> 12:37.883
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:39.885 --> 12:41.553
<i>Nagata here.</i>

12:41.553 --> 12:43.722
This is Fayez Sarkis
on the <i>Edward Israel.</i>

12:43.722 --> 12:45.223
I have an anomaly
on the surface.

12:45.223 --> 12:46.933
Can I get a look
at any surface data

12:46.933 --> 12:48.602
the <i>Rocinante</i> has made?

12:48.602 --> 12:49.936
Your boss, Murtry,

12:49.936 --> 12:51.646
was shooting at me
not long ago.

12:51.646 --> 12:53.982
He's not my boss, and...

12:55.901 --> 12:57.360
<i>...he's kind of an ass.</i>

12:57.360 --> 12:59.821
<i>I'm just looking to fill
some gaps in the data</i>

12:59.821 --> 13:01.573
<i>from when we orbited
to the far side of the planet.</i>

13:01.573 --> 13:02.949
<i>I can send you
the coordinates.</i>

13:05.994 --> 13:08.497
All right.
Send them along.

13:12.918 --> 13:14.586
Yo, <i>Rocinante</i> here.

13:14.586 --> 13:16.546
<i>I want to talk to my wife.
Where is she?</i>

13:16.546 --> 13:18.715
Oh, hey, Jakob.
Uh, yeah, she's here,

13:18.715 --> 13:21.176
<i>- and she is all right.</i>
- I didn't ask if she was

13:21.176 --> 13:22.886
all right!
I said I need to talk to her!

13:22.886 --> 13:25.764
<i>Okay, uh,
cool your jets there, friend.</i>

13:25.764 --> 13:28.141
<i>I'll transfer you over.</i>

13:28.141 --> 13:29.351
[intercom warbles]

13:29.351 --> 13:30.977
<i>[Alex] Hey, Lucia.</i>

13:30.977 --> 13:33.730
<i>Your husband...
he wants to talk to you.</i>

13:44.241 --> 13:46.326
[sighs]

13:48.620 --> 13:50.288
<i>Tell me she's somewhere safe,</i>

13:50.288 --> 13:52.332
<i>that she's not with you.</i>

13:52.332 --> 13:53.792
What?
Who?

13:53.792 --> 13:54.793
Felcia.

13:54.793 --> 13:55.835
Our daughter!

13:55.835 --> 13:57.879
Tell me you know where she is!

13:57.879 --> 14:00.173
<i>Jakob, I don't.</i>

14:00.173 --> 14:02.008
<i>Maybe she hid
when the shooting started.</i>

14:02.008 --> 14:05.220
<i>- I'm sure she'll be...</i>
- I have been everyplace!

14:05.220 --> 14:06.930
She's not here!

14:06.930 --> 14:09.599
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

14:09.599 --> 14:10.934
Oh, God.

14:10.934 --> 14:12.477
Murtry.

14:12.477 --> 14:14.688
- Uh, he said...
<i>[Jakob] What?</i>

14:14.688 --> 14:15.647
<i>What did he say?</i>

14:15.647 --> 14:17.482
Uh, nothing specific.

14:17.482 --> 14:18.775
When he was telling me
to surrender,

14:18.775 --> 14:20.151
he talked about you...

14:21.528 --> 14:22.946
...and her.

14:24.114 --> 14:26.408
It's true, then,

14:26.408 --> 14:28.285
what they're saying
about you and Coop,

14:28.285 --> 14:30.078
Scotty, the others.

14:31.079 --> 14:32.581
You were part of that.

14:33.748 --> 14:36.209
We were just trying
to put them off,

14:36.209 --> 14:37.877
slow them down
until we could get

14:37.877 --> 14:39.504
a load of ore out,

14:39.504 --> 14:41.423
<i>get some money,
hire a lawyer, maybe.</i>

14:41.423 --> 14:42.882
<i>No one was supposed
to get hurt.</i>

14:42.882 --> 14:44.467
God damn it, Lucia.

14:44.467 --> 14:45.719
How could you be so stupid?

14:45.719 --> 14:48.388
I wasn't stupid!

14:48.388 --> 14:49.931
I did it for us!

14:49.931 --> 14:51.683
<i>All of us!</i>

14:51.683 --> 14:53.602
Someone had to be strong.

14:53.602 --> 14:55.854
And I wasn't?

14:55.854 --> 14:58.273
I wasn't strong enough

14:58.273 --> 15:01.151
because I didn't want to bring
the killing to this planet,

15:01.151 --> 15:03.528
<i>- like Coop and his OPA thugs?</i>
- Stop.

15:03.528 --> 15:05.155
You don't get to tell me
when to stop.

15:05.155 --> 15:06.615
<i>You ran away.</i>

15:06.615 --> 15:09.534
<i>My daughter is missing.</i>

15:09.534 --> 15:11.328
<i>Now they're going
to round us up like cattle</i>

15:11.328 --> 15:12.495
<i>and take us away!</i>

15:12.495 --> 15:14.164
<i>We have nothing!</i>

15:15.165 --> 15:17.626
Not even our family.

15:17.626 --> 15:23.632
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:23.632 --> 15:25.133
You can't let them
make us leave.

15:25.967 --> 15:27.552
We have nowhere else to go.

15:27.552 --> 15:28.803
You have to fight!

15:31.556 --> 15:33.933
Jakob, you have to fight.

15:33.933 --> 15:35.935
If we did all that

15:35.935 --> 15:38.313
and it doesn't even matter?

15:38.313 --> 15:40.523
You have to stay.

15:43.985 --> 15:46.196
All these terrible things
you've done?

15:47.781 --> 15:49.824
They didn't save us.

15:49.824 --> 15:51.785
[exhales heavily]

15:52.661 --> 15:56.247
All they did was destroy
the only thing we had left.

15:56.247 --> 16:03.254
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:06.341 --> 16:07.884
Oh.

16:20.188 --> 16:21.731
[groans softly]

16:21.731 --> 16:28.738
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:40.291 --> 16:41.418
[exhales heavily]

16:43.253 --> 16:50.260
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:54.139 --> 16:55.306
Trouble coming.

16:56.683 --> 16:59.686
[faint indistinct chatter]

17:01.312 --> 17:02.564
Looks like it.

17:04.899 --> 17:06.025
[man] Okay.

17:06.025 --> 17:07.360
[man] Bring it out.

17:07.360 --> 17:09.070
You need to do
anything about it?

17:09.070 --> 17:11.865
No orders.
Just staying ready.

17:11.865 --> 17:14.075
Watching your ass
is always a good idea.

17:14.075 --> 17:16.661
Oh, you hitting on me?

17:16.661 --> 17:18.955
Not right now.

17:18.955 --> 17:20.457
Disappointing.

17:21.750 --> 17:24.753
[indistinct chatter]

17:28.798 --> 17:31.801
<i>[tense music]</i>

17:31.801 --> 17:38.808
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:40.143 --> 17:42.270
Oh, my Earther sweethearts.

17:42.270 --> 17:43.730
[Liam] What the fuck
do you want?

17:43.730 --> 17:46.357
[all grunting]

17:46.357 --> 17:51.488
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:53.364 --> 17:55.116
You!

17:55.116 --> 17:56.284
I want to talk to you.

17:56.284 --> 17:57.952
This isn't a great time.

17:57.952 --> 17:59.412
I don't care.

18:00.246 --> 18:01.581
You seem angry.

18:03.875 --> 18:04.709
At me?

18:11.049 --> 18:12.300
[Holden clears throat]

18:15.011 --> 18:17.972
I've been going through
everything that happened:

18:17.972 --> 18:21.434
the bugs that showed up
exactly when you did,

18:21.434 --> 18:23.353
the lightning and the way
you happened to be

18:23.353 --> 18:25.814
exactly where
the lightning started,

18:25.814 --> 18:27.732
the underground structures,

18:27.732 --> 18:29.400
the digging machine.

18:29.400 --> 18:31.653
None of this happened
until you showed up,

18:31.653 --> 18:34.239
and when I ask you about it,
you deflect.

18:34.239 --> 18:35.782
It's complicated.

18:35.782 --> 18:37.826
Yes, exactly like that.

18:37.826 --> 18:39.118
- It's just...
- Complicated,

18:39.118 --> 18:40.829
need-to-know,
none of my business.

18:40.829 --> 18:42.372
Enough of that shit!

18:43.289 --> 18:44.958
You are connected to this,

18:44.958 --> 18:47.252
and you are
withholding information.

18:51.172 --> 18:53.216
You're right.

18:53.216 --> 18:55.593
And yeah,
there are some things

18:55.593 --> 18:56.845
I've kept to myself.

18:56.845 --> 18:58.096
Well?

18:58.096 --> 18:59.556
I wouldn't even know
where to begin.

18:59.556 --> 19:00.849
Oh, for fuck's sake.

19:00.849 --> 19:02.308
- [gunfire]
- [people yelling]

19:02.308 --> 19:03.893
Were those gunshots?

19:03.893 --> 19:05.270
- [gunfire, glass shatters]
[Holden] Down!

19:05.270 --> 19:07.605
[gunfire continues]

19:07.605 --> 19:10.108
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

19:10.108 --> 19:11.860
[Wei] Let them go right now!

19:11.860 --> 19:13.111
[Liam] Fuck these assholes.
Just shoot them!

19:13.111 --> 19:14.487
[Angeletti] <i>Na wanya</i> do that,

19:14.487 --> 19:15.488
unless you <i>wanya</i> to see

19:15.488 --> 19:17.782
the inside of his head.

19:17.782 --> 19:19.200
Don't make me ask again.

19:19.200 --> 19:22.203
<i>[tense music]</i>

19:22.203 --> 19:28.626
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:28.626 --> 19:31.045
- [gunfire]
- [people yelling]

19:31.045 --> 19:33.006
[gunshots]

19:33.006 --> 19:34.007
[Wei] Covering fire!

19:34.007 --> 19:35.842
Fall back! Fall back!

19:35.842 --> 19:38.845
[indistinct chatter]

19:41.556 --> 19:44.726
[man] If you want your friends
alive, you stop shooting!

19:44.726 --> 19:46.185
What the hell happened?

19:46.185 --> 19:48.062
Fucking Belters
grabbed two of my people.

19:48.062 --> 19:50.064
They're holding them
in the trading post.

19:50.064 --> 19:52.191
Half a dozen more are armed
and in cover outside.

19:52.191 --> 19:53.776
Looks like they're just
holding their ground.

19:53.776 --> 19:55.194
Any demands?

19:55.194 --> 19:56.446
- [device beeps]
- What are they hoping

19:56.446 --> 19:57.572
to accomplish with this?

19:57.572 --> 19:58.907
[device beeps]

19:59.866 --> 20:01.868
<i>Our people have been locked
in their quarters</i>

20:01.868 --> 20:03.828
<i>by corporate soldiers,</i>

20:03.828 --> 20:05.997
<i>they have been executed
without trial,</i>

20:05.997 --> 20:08.833
<i>and now we are being ordered
to evacuate.</i>

20:08.833 --> 20:11.544
<i>We won't stop
anyone else from leaving.</i>

20:11.544 --> 20:12.879
<i>They can go in peace.</i>

20:12.879 --> 20:14.631
<i>But we will not be forced</i>

20:14.631 --> 20:16.716
<i>from our homes again.</i>

20:16.716 --> 20:19.093
Is this just us,
or is she broadcasting this?

20:19.093 --> 20:20.970
I don't see why she wouldn't.

20:20.970 --> 20:22.555
Chances are, tomorrow,

20:22.555 --> 20:25.058
it'll be all over
the news feeds back home.

20:25.058 --> 20:26.726
Fantastic.

20:29.646 --> 20:31.481
You look like you're having
a good time.

20:31.481 --> 20:35.401
[sighs] I do enjoy the clarity
of these moments.

20:36.194 --> 20:38.571
Now you see
what I've been working with:

20:38.571 --> 20:41.449
professional victims
and martyrs.

20:41.449 --> 20:43.534
But not a word about the bombs
that they've thrown,

20:43.534 --> 20:45.119
the bodies
they've stacked up.

20:45.870 --> 20:46.829
I scouted their position.

20:46.829 --> 20:47.830
They're dug in tight,

20:47.830 --> 20:49.582
but we can root them out.

20:49.582 --> 20:51.793
I feel like this is exactly
what you hoped would happen.

20:51.793 --> 20:54.545
I'd love to have come
to a peaceful resolution,

20:54.545 --> 20:57.507
but then they took
two RCE employees hostage,

20:57.507 --> 20:59.050
and keeping them alive
is my job.

20:59.050 --> 21:00.426
[Holden] We'll get
your people back.

21:00.426 --> 21:01.719
Don't even think
about using this

21:01.719 --> 21:03.554
as an excuse
for a massacre.

21:03.554 --> 21:05.515
No,

21:05.515 --> 21:08.142
but I am gonna gas
every Belter in the camp,

21:08.142 --> 21:09.435
anyone I find with a gun

21:09.435 --> 21:11.729
is gonna be disarmed
and restrained,

21:11.729 --> 21:13.773
and the rest
will be kept sedated

21:13.773 --> 21:15.149
until they can be taken
up to their ship

21:15.149 --> 21:16.651
and sent on their way.

21:16.651 --> 21:18.611
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

21:18.611 --> 21:20.905
I would ask
if you have any objection,

21:20.905 --> 21:25.118
but I honestly
don't give a fuck now.

21:25.118 --> 21:31.082
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:36.754 --> 21:39.757
[applause]

21:41.467 --> 21:43.511
<i>[moderator] Tonight's debate
will be town hall style</i>

21:43.511 --> 21:45.346
<i>with questions selected</i>

21:45.346 --> 21:47.432
<i>by a nonpartisan committee
from around the world.</i>

21:47.432 --> 21:49.851
<i>We ask the candidates
to keep their answers brief</i>

21:49.851 --> 21:51.894
<i>and on topic.</i>

21:51.894 --> 21:53.396
<i>Our first question comes</i>

21:53.396 --> 21:54.647
<i>from the North American
trade zone.</i>

21:56.190 --> 21:57.942
<i>With all the uncertainty</i>

21:57.942 --> 22:00.445
<i>regarding the alien worlds
outside the Ring,</i>

22:00.445 --> 22:03.156
<i>I want to ask the candidates
how they would protect us</i>

22:03.156 --> 22:04.907
<i>from a second Eros incident.</i>

22:04.907 --> 22:06.576
That's a very good question.

22:06.576 --> 22:09.203
The Eros incident
was a frightening moment

22:09.203 --> 22:10.621
for all of us.

22:10.621 --> 22:13.458
It was also an opening
to a new era.

22:13.458 --> 22:16.794
The existence of alien life
gives us,

22:16.794 --> 22:18.171
all of us,

22:18.171 --> 22:20.423
unimaginable opportunities,

22:20.423 --> 22:22.008
and I think the real danger
of Eros

22:22.008 --> 22:24.802
is that we only react to it
from fear.

22:24.802 --> 22:26.262
What we need now is leadership

22:26.262 --> 22:28.306
that can embrace
the possibilities

22:28.306 --> 22:30.725
while managing the risks.

22:34.645 --> 22:36.773
I was in the situation room

22:36.773 --> 22:38.107
during the Eros incident,

22:38.107 --> 22:41.069
and as I recall,
the real danger

22:41.069 --> 22:44.655
was that it was about
to kill everyone on Earth.

22:44.655 --> 22:48.951
I helped avert that disaster,
and afterward,

22:48.951 --> 22:50.453
I brought to justice

22:50.453 --> 22:53.331
the men who weaponized
the Protomolecule.

22:53.331 --> 22:56.167
You ask
how I would protect Earth

22:56.167 --> 22:58.044
from another Eros incident?

22:58.044 --> 22:59.545
That's a good question,

22:59.545 --> 23:01.631
and here is my answer:

23:01.631 --> 23:04.425
the same way I did last time.

23:04.425 --> 23:07.053
[audience murmuring]

23:07.053 --> 23:08.596
<i>[moderator]
Our next question comes</i>

23:08.596 --> 23:10.098
<i>from the Eurasia trade zone.</i>

23:10.890 --> 23:12.558
<i>[man] I'm
a medical technician,</i>

23:12.558 --> 23:14.977
<i>and I believe
health care infrastructure</i>

23:14.977 --> 23:16.813
<i>is underfunded
when it comes to dealing</i>

23:16.813 --> 23:18.940
<i>with the undocumented
population.</i>

23:18.940 --> 23:20.775
<i>Murtry's waiting
until he has a plan</i>

23:20.775 --> 23:23.319
<i>for rescuing his people
in the trading post.</i>

23:23.319 --> 23:25.113
<i>Unless we find
some other solution</i>

23:25.113 --> 23:26.405
<i>before then,
he's gonna move forward</i>

23:26.405 --> 23:27.740
<i>with gassing the camp.</i>

23:28.991 --> 23:30.660
Would you actually let him
do that?

23:30.660 --> 23:32.495
<i>[Holden] At this point,
I'm not sure he's wrong.</i>

23:32.495 --> 23:35.039
What were they thinking,
taking hostages like that?

23:35.039 --> 23:36.457
<i>[Naomi] What about Miller?</i>

23:36.457 --> 23:38.209
Any contact at all?

23:39.168 --> 23:41.838
Nothing.
[sighs]

23:41.838 --> 23:44.465
But it's clear he's caused

23:44.465 --> 23:47.635
everything that has happened
since we arrived.

23:47.635 --> 23:49.804
Can't let the settlers die
because of that.

23:49.804 --> 23:52.348
<i>So Murtry forcing them out
is the answer?</i>

23:52.348 --> 23:54.183
You know I don't want
to do this at gunpoint,

23:54.183 --> 23:55.643
but I have to do something.

23:55.643 --> 23:57.728
Murtry has no right
making them leave,

23:57.728 --> 23:59.188
and neither do you.

23:59.188 --> 24:01.357
<i>If they die here, it's on me.</i>

24:03.025 --> 24:06.112
And it's on the Inners
for fighting over Ganymede

24:06.112 --> 24:08.406
and Jules-Pierre Mao
for his experiments

24:08.406 --> 24:09.949
and Avasarala
for sending us

24:09.949 --> 24:11.701
and some aliens

24:11.701 --> 24:13.161
for creating the Protomolecule

24:13.161 --> 24:14.912
and shooting it at Earth.

24:16.747 --> 24:19.333
And it's on the Belters too...

24:21.002 --> 24:23.254
...for coming here,

24:23.254 --> 24:26.048
<i>for staying
after you warned them,</i>

24:26.048 --> 24:28.259
for taking hostages now.

24:30.261 --> 24:31.679
They're not children.

24:33.264 --> 24:37.226
They have no idea
what's really going on here.

24:37.226 --> 24:39.812
They're still playing out
the old squabbles.

24:40.605 --> 24:42.440
Don't decide for them.

24:43.608 --> 24:45.401
Tell them the truth

24:45.401 --> 24:47.528
and let them decide
for themselves.

24:49.697 --> 24:51.991
You know, I used to be the one
saying things like that.

24:54.243 --> 24:57.330
<i>So go be you.</i>

25:01.375 --> 25:03.711
Lucia?
Hey.

25:03.711 --> 25:05.421
I don't know if you're hungry
or nothing,

25:05.421 --> 25:09.258
but, um, post-op,
you gotta eat, right?

25:09.258 --> 25:13.262
So, uh, I took it upon myself
and made you a little broth.

25:15.473 --> 25:17.934
Lucia?
You all right in there?

25:19.685 --> 25:20.853
Hmm.

25:24.649 --> 25:27.652
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

25:27.652 --> 25:29.528
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:29.528 --> 25:31.864
Door lock override.

25:31.864 --> 25:33.199
Yeah, all right,
I'm not trying

25:33.199 --> 25:34.742
to intrude upon you
or nothing.

25:34.742 --> 25:36.118
I just thought
you might enjoy a little...

25:36.118 --> 25:40.039
[monitor beeping]

25:40.039 --> 25:42.041
Naomi!

25:42.041 --> 25:44.877
[auto-doc beeping]

25:44.877 --> 25:46.254
Her pulse is weak.

25:46.254 --> 25:48.214
Yeah, she's got
no more blood left in her.

25:48.214 --> 25:49.340
She's shutting down.

25:49.340 --> 25:50.424
Stop.

25:50.424 --> 25:51.842
It's fine.

25:51.842 --> 25:53.427
[monitor beeping]

25:53.427 --> 25:56.138
Oh, Christ.
She popped a bleeder in there.

25:56.138 --> 25:57.932
Okay.

25:57.932 --> 26:00.351
You get it stopped,

26:00.351 --> 26:02.061
and I'll run
a second infusion line.

26:02.061 --> 26:04.188
- Now!
- Right.

26:04.188 --> 26:06.649
[monitors beeping]

26:06.649 --> 26:09.443
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

26:09.443 --> 26:11.988
Okay.

26:11.988 --> 26:15.032
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:15.032 --> 26:16.367
- [screams]
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

26:16.367 --> 26:17.576
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

26:17.576 --> 26:18.995
I just gotta...I gotta...

26:20.788 --> 26:21.831
- Okay.
- [groans]

26:21.831 --> 26:23.499
[Alex] Gotcha.

26:23.499 --> 26:24.959
I don't even know what the hell
I'm looking for in here.

26:24.959 --> 26:26.168
That's all right.

26:26.168 --> 26:27.586
Your abdomen
is full of blood.

26:27.586 --> 26:29.588
I can't see anything.

26:29.588 --> 26:32.008
Lucia, listen to me.
I need your help, okay?

26:32.008 --> 26:34.176
I've never done this before.

26:34.176 --> 26:36.429
Please, you gotta tell me
what to do.

26:36.429 --> 26:40.349
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:40.349 --> 26:41.934
Help me, please.

26:41.934 --> 26:43.853
No, no.

26:43.853 --> 26:45.896
Don't help me.

26:45.896 --> 26:47.064
God damn it.

26:47.064 --> 26:48.774
[monitors beeping rapidly]

26:48.774 --> 26:50.401
Look, do not make me

26:50.401 --> 26:52.403
tell your daughter
I had to let you die!

26:52.403 --> 26:54.030
Fucking tell me what to do!

26:54.030 --> 26:59.785
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:59.785 --> 27:00.870
Suction.

27:02.204 --> 27:04.915
All right, suction.
All right.

27:04.915 --> 27:07.001
- [Lucia screams]
[Alex] Sorry.

27:07.001 --> 27:08.085
Sorry.

27:08.085 --> 27:09.378
Where's that line, Naomi?

27:09.378 --> 27:10.588
I'm working on it.

27:10.588 --> 27:12.173
[groans]

27:12.173 --> 27:14.550
Uh, all right.
You're still bleeding inside.

27:14.550 --> 27:15.551
How do I stop that?

27:15.551 --> 27:18.179
[panting]

27:18.179 --> 27:19.138
[grunts]

27:19.138 --> 27:20.973
There.
There.

27:22.683 --> 27:23.934
It's in.

27:23.934 --> 27:25.227
The infusion's working.

27:25.227 --> 27:27.313
You just gotta stop
the bleeder now.

27:29.398 --> 27:30.358
I can do this.

27:30.358 --> 27:31.317
Don't!

27:31.317 --> 27:32.943
You don't have to.

27:32.943 --> 27:35.029
[Lucia crying]

27:37.239 --> 27:38.574
[groans]

27:38.574 --> 27:40.159
You're too low.

27:40.159 --> 27:41.285
Okay, all right.

27:41.285 --> 27:48.292
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:50.086 --> 27:51.629
[yelps]

27:51.629 --> 27:56.175
[groaning]

27:56.175 --> 27:57.551
[monitor chimes]

27:57.551 --> 27:58.677
Hey.

27:59.929 --> 28:01.430
I got it.

28:01.430 --> 28:03.391
I got it.
[laughs]

28:03.391 --> 28:05.184
[Lucia breathing raggedly]

28:05.184 --> 28:07.812
<i>[soft music]</i>

28:07.812 --> 28:09.063
[laughs]

28:10.981 --> 28:13.818
Hey, you did good.

28:13.818 --> 28:15.069
Thank you.

28:15.694 --> 28:18.406
[Naomi] I'll, um,
start the cleanup.

28:18.406 --> 28:19.740
You stay with her.

28:23.702 --> 28:25.454
You're gonna be all right.

28:27.164 --> 28:28.874
Sorry I yelled at you.

28:31.794 --> 28:34.213
I can't even die right.

28:34.213 --> 28:37.174
[cries]

28:37.174 --> 28:42.263
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:42.263 --> 28:44.265
[Amos] They got
a solid position,

28:44.265 --> 28:46.308
good cover,
overlapping fire.

28:46.308 --> 28:49.019
That's a meat grinder.

28:49.019 --> 28:51.730
If Murtry orders you
to go in,

28:51.730 --> 28:53.107
don't go.

28:54.316 --> 28:58.195
Comes to that, I guarantee
they'll bleed more than we do.

28:58.195 --> 28:59.864
If you say so.

29:02.032 --> 29:04.076
Nice working
on the same side for once.

29:05.494 --> 29:07.288
Fuck that.

29:07.288 --> 29:10.082
I'm not gassing anybody
on Murtry's orders.

29:10.082 --> 29:12.918
I just don't want
to see you get shot over this.

29:18.007 --> 29:21.802
<i>[tense music]</i>

29:21.802 --> 29:23.512
I'm unarmed!

29:23.512 --> 29:25.097
Oh, shit.

29:25.097 --> 29:26.640
What's he doing?

29:26.640 --> 29:28.100
Being him.

29:30.728 --> 29:32.396
What do you want?

29:32.396 --> 29:35.149
I want to talk.

29:35.149 --> 29:36.817
<i>[woman] I've been
on the basic rolls</i>

29:36.817 --> 29:38.360
<i>since I was born,</i>

29:38.360 --> 29:39.987
<i>and I've been
on the waiting list</i>

29:39.987 --> 29:41.906
<i>for vocational training
and job placement</i>

29:41.906 --> 29:43.616
<i>for 30 years.</i>

29:43.616 --> 29:45.743
<i>I want to ask the candidates,
what can be done</i>

29:45.743 --> 29:48.621
<i>to offer more opportunity
to those on basic assistance?</i>

29:48.621 --> 29:52.500
There is no law or policy
so well-made

29:52.500 --> 29:54.793
that a culture of shortcuts,

29:54.793 --> 29:56.587
preferential treatment,
and corruption

29:56.587 --> 29:59.423
cannot degrade it.

29:59.423 --> 30:00.966
Any change we make

30:00.966 --> 30:03.719
must be rooted in fairness.

30:03.719 --> 30:06.430
It has been well documented
at this point

30:06.430 --> 30:09.892
that my opponent exploited
political connections

30:09.892 --> 30:12.311
to jump the line
and take the spot

30:12.311 --> 30:13.729
that would have gone
to someone

30:13.729 --> 30:16.857
with fewer friends
in high places.

30:16.857 --> 30:19.193
I have already requested
changes

30:19.193 --> 30:21.654
that would close that loophole

30:21.654 --> 30:24.782
and make the system fair again.

30:28.077 --> 30:29.870
It's a little strange

30:29.870 --> 30:33.165
to have a member
of the political aristocracy

30:33.165 --> 30:36.252
lecture me about connections.

30:36.252 --> 30:38.504
Tonight's the first time
she's ever interviewed

30:38.504 --> 30:39.838
for a job.

30:39.838 --> 30:42.174
[scattered laughter]

30:42.174 --> 30:43.592
[Gao] But she's right.

30:43.592 --> 30:45.177
My parents had friends
who helped me

30:45.177 --> 30:47.179
get a lottery placement.

30:47.179 --> 30:48.889
My opponent has asked

30:48.889 --> 30:51.141
what happened to the person
whose place I took.

30:51.141 --> 30:54.353
<i>[warm music]</i>

30:54.353 --> 30:57.690
George,
would you stand up, please?

30:57.690 --> 30:59.400
George Cantor
was my first alternate.

30:59.400 --> 31:01.735
When I got my appointment
at the regional government,

31:01.735 --> 31:04.905
I hired George to work
with my policy research team.

31:06.323 --> 31:07.866
He now runs it.

31:07.866 --> 31:11.287
My second alternate
was a woman named Li Fan.

31:11.287 --> 31:14.206
She has become
my top security consultant.

31:15.249 --> 31:18.460
My third alternate
was Cristof Hymer.

31:18.460 --> 31:20.254
Sadly, he died of an overdose

31:20.254 --> 31:23.382
and never got off the rolls.

31:23.382 --> 31:25.593
George and Fan
would both have had

31:25.593 --> 31:28.887
to fail for him
to get a chance,

31:28.887 --> 31:30.472
because that's the lie,

31:30.472 --> 31:32.182
isn't it?

31:32.182 --> 31:35.519
Six thousand people
fight for one slot,

31:35.519 --> 31:37.938
and we say anyone can make it.

31:37.938 --> 31:40.357
Any one of those 6,000,

31:40.357 --> 31:44.612
not two, not ten.

31:44.612 --> 31:46.822
Certainly not everyone.

31:46.822 --> 31:49.033
We all know
the system's broken.

31:49.033 --> 31:50.868
We all just want a chance.

31:50.868 --> 31:53.329
We aren't afraid
to work hard.

31:53.329 --> 31:55.706
We aren't afraid
to take risks,

31:55.706 --> 31:58.083
and with 1,300
new solar systems,

31:58.083 --> 31:59.752
we can provide
that opportunity

31:59.752 --> 32:03.047
for everyone,
not just the colonists:

32:03.047 --> 32:07.426
workers and farmers
and engineers.

32:08.719 --> 32:10.638
The people of Earth
have talent

32:10.638 --> 32:12.014
and drive and ambition.

32:12.014 --> 32:13.349
What we need...

32:15.059 --> 32:16.852
...what we deserve...

32:16.852 --> 32:19.688
is a government
that gives us a chance.

32:19.688 --> 32:21.857
- [applause]
- [intercom beeps]

32:21.857 --> 32:23.484
<i>[woman] Security alert.</i>
[guard] Ma'am.

32:23.484 --> 32:25.819
We need you to come with us
right away.

32:25.819 --> 32:27.696
<i>[woman] Please remain where
you are until further notice.</i>

32:27.696 --> 32:29.615
Archangel secured.
Exiting now.

32:29.615 --> 32:31.533
What the fuck
is wrong with you?

32:31.533 --> 32:33.035
Can you not see where I am?

32:33.035 --> 32:34.328
We have
a security situation.

32:34.328 --> 32:35.454
Shit.

32:35.454 --> 32:38.332
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

32:42.378 --> 32:45.381
<i>[tense music]</i>

32:45.381 --> 32:47.758
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:47.758 --> 32:49.551
What are we looking at?

32:51.220 --> 32:53.389
Three hours ago,
this ship went off its course.

32:53.389 --> 32:55.474
The transponder
IDs her as the <i>Sinon,</i>

32:55.474 --> 32:56.975
- out of Triton.
- And its path?

32:56.975 --> 32:58.602
It was heading
towards Luna,

32:58.602 --> 33:00.145
but 20 minutes ago,
it shifted.

33:00.145 --> 33:02.439
It's on a collision course
with Sentinel Nineteen.

33:02.439 --> 33:04.233
The asteroid spotter?

33:04.233 --> 33:06.860
You rushed me off the surface
of the planet,

33:06.860 --> 33:08.153
so obviously,
you're treating this

33:08.153 --> 33:09.738
like an attack.

33:09.738 --> 33:10.906
What's the threat assessment?

33:10.906 --> 33:12.741
A ship's drive
is a fusion bomb,

33:12.741 --> 33:15.202
and it's targeting
our early warning system.

33:15.202 --> 33:16.412
Protocol is to assume

33:16.412 --> 33:17.871
there is more than one
on its way.

33:17.871 --> 33:19.331
So why haven't we killed
the ship already?

33:23.043 --> 33:25.295
<i>[man] This is the</i> Sinon.
<i>We are experiencing</i>

33:25.295 --> 33:27.673
<i>a minor failure
in our computer systems.</i>

33:27.673 --> 33:29.842
<i>It has affected our comms
and drive controls.</i>

33:29.842 --> 33:31.635
<i>We are working to correct it.
We have children on board.</i>

33:31.635 --> 33:33.095
This message was sent

33:33.095 --> 33:34.430
ten minutes
after it went off course.

33:34.430 --> 33:37.015
We haven't been able
to raise them since.

33:37.015 --> 33:38.517
How long before we have
to make a decision?

33:38.517 --> 33:40.644
If we kill it now,
there's a three percent chance

33:40.644 --> 33:42.062
the debris field
will compromise

33:42.062 --> 33:43.731
our strategic defenses.

33:43.731 --> 33:45.482
The longer we wait,
the more that goes up.

33:45.482 --> 33:48.193
Or maybe we blow up a ship
full of innocent civilians

33:48.193 --> 33:49.778
who just called for help.

33:49.778 --> 33:54.450
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:54.450 --> 33:56.660
- [device beeps]
- Ma'am, we cannot afford...

33:56.660 --> 33:57.661
[aide] Ma'am,
we just got a flash

33:57.661 --> 33:59.204
from signal intelligence.

33:59.204 --> 34:00.914
The drive signature on record

34:00.914 --> 34:03.417
also matches a colony ship
called the <i>Sojourner.</i>

34:03.417 --> 34:05.878
The one the Belters said
was lost to scrap?

34:07.129 --> 34:10.132
<i>[tense music]</i>

34:10.132 --> 34:15.220
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:15.220 --> 34:18.265
Kill it.
Destroy the ship immediately.

34:18.265 --> 34:19.183
Yes, ma'am.

34:19.183 --> 34:26.190
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:48.253 --> 34:49.922
<i>This supposed attack</i>

34:49.922 --> 34:52.174
<i>never should've happened
in the first place.</i>

34:52.174 --> 34:54.134
<i>If we were supporting
colony ships</i>

34:54.134 --> 34:56.303
<i>instead of stranding them
out where they're easy prey</i>

34:56.303 --> 34:58.722
<i>for piracy,</i>

34:58.722 --> 35:00.390
<i>it wouldn't have.</i>

35:01.391 --> 35:03.060
It was bad timing.

35:03.060 --> 35:04.645
It could've happened
to anyone.

35:04.645 --> 35:07.648
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

35:07.648 --> 35:14.655
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:24.248 --> 35:26.333
[door hisses]

35:28.460 --> 35:29.711
How are you feeling?

35:30.754 --> 35:32.589
Weak.

35:32.589 --> 35:34.424
Do you mind if I come in?

35:34.424 --> 35:36.176
It's your ship.

35:46.562 --> 35:49.231
I didn't deserve
to be saved.

35:50.941 --> 35:53.819
Deserving isn't really
the issue.

35:53.819 --> 35:55.529
Maybe it should be.

35:59.575 --> 36:01.118
It's funny.

36:01.118 --> 36:02.828
I was just talking
with Holden

36:02.828 --> 36:06.039
about letting people
make their own choices,

36:06.039 --> 36:09.001
even if you don't agree
with them,

36:09.001 --> 36:11.753
and now...

36:11.753 --> 36:14.131
Regrets?

36:14.131 --> 36:15.966
No,

36:15.966 --> 36:18.677
'cause I've been
where you are right now.

36:18.677 --> 36:21.305
I don't think that you have.

36:26.101 --> 36:28.854
I was young
and in love with a boy

36:28.854 --> 36:30.856
who had a crazy plan.

36:32.357 --> 36:35.777
I'd hack
reactor control programs.

36:35.777 --> 36:39.531
He had a way to insert them
into Inner ships.

36:39.531 --> 36:40.991
Then we could turn off
the drive,

36:40.991 --> 36:43.410
leave them on the drift,

36:43.410 --> 36:45.454
rescue them for a price later,

36:45.454 --> 36:47.331
and it wouldn't look
like piracy

36:47.331 --> 36:51.126
because they'd be so grateful
that we saved them.

36:51.126 --> 36:53.170
<i>[melancholy music]</i>

36:53.170 --> 36:57.591
At least, that was
the story he told me.

36:59.885 --> 37:02.971
The first one we tried
was the <i>Augustín Gamarra.</i>

37:04.514 --> 37:06.808
I know that name.

37:06.808 --> 37:08.644
Why do I know that name?

37:09.895 --> 37:13.190
It was the one that blew up
in the docks at Luna...

37:15.025 --> 37:16.944
...because the man I loved,

37:16.944 --> 37:19.446
the father of my child,

37:19.446 --> 37:23.158
used my code
to overload the reactor.

37:24.910 --> 37:27.079
We killed 516 people.

37:29.873 --> 37:31.959
And he meant to do it again.

37:35.045 --> 37:37.881
It wasn't your doing, then.

37:37.881 --> 37:39.424
You were tricked.

37:40.425 --> 37:42.260
I chose what I did.

37:45.138 --> 37:46.890
I chose not to see

37:46.890 --> 37:50.644
what kind of man my lover was
until it was too late.

37:51.645 --> 37:55.524
Then when I told him
I'd never help him again,

37:55.524 --> 37:57.609
it was the last time

37:57.609 --> 38:00.153
he let me see my little boy.

38:02.614 --> 38:04.408
I'm sorry for that.

38:05.450 --> 38:07.828
I almost walked out
an air lock.

38:08.912 --> 38:12.165
Being dead seemed better.

38:12.165 --> 38:13.625
I'm sorry.

38:13.625 --> 38:17.504
Stop saying you're sorry.

38:17.504 --> 38:19.589
I'm not asking for sympathy.

38:19.589 --> 38:21.800
I'm telling you something
you need to know

38:21.800 --> 38:23.385
if you're going to live.

38:23.385 --> 38:25.512
I don't understand.

38:25.512 --> 38:28.515
I have a family now.

38:28.515 --> 38:31.184
Certainly not one
I would've expected,

38:31.184 --> 38:34.479
but I love them,

38:34.479 --> 38:36.231
and they love me.

38:37.357 --> 38:40.485
And I have a life

38:40.485 --> 38:42.362
that I like living.

38:43.989 --> 38:47.409
I haven't had that,

38:47.409 --> 38:49.703
not in years.

38:49.703 --> 38:53.874
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:53.874 --> 38:56.793
If you want to die,

38:56.793 --> 38:58.670
I can't stop you,

38:58.670 --> 39:01.965
but there is a path

39:01.965 --> 39:03.967
from where you are

39:03.967 --> 39:05.761
to where I am.

39:07.345 --> 39:10.432
All we did was buy you
a little time.

39:11.975 --> 39:15.979
You decide what you want
to do with it.

39:15.979 --> 39:22.986
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:25.906 --> 39:29.076
[door hisses]

39:29.076 --> 39:33.955
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:33.955 --> 39:35.624
[Holden] I know there's
already been bloodshed

39:35.624 --> 39:36.708
and both sides
have lost people.

39:36.708 --> 39:37.959
[Murtry] I didn't lose anyone.

39:37.959 --> 39:39.294
I've got two of mine
at gunpoint

39:39.294 --> 39:40.712
in that building right there.

39:40.712 --> 39:42.756
[Angeletti] Get the fuck
off our planet!

39:42.756 --> 39:44.549
<i>Deng</i> we send your people
back to you unharmed.

39:44.549 --> 39:46.051
[Jakob] What did you do
to my daughter,

39:46.051 --> 39:47.469
you son of a bitch, huh?

39:47.469 --> 39:49.304
We never touched your damn kid!

39:49.304 --> 39:51.306
How would we know?
You kill us for no reason.

39:51.306 --> 39:53.517
[people clamoring]

39:53.517 --> 39:55.685
[Holden] God damn it!
Everyone shut up for a minute!

39:55.685 --> 39:57.229
[woman] This is my home here!

39:57.229 --> 39:58.814
[woman] There's no way.

40:02.526 --> 40:04.569
I know no one wants
to back down.

40:04.569 --> 40:06.446
I know why all of you came
to this place

40:06.446 --> 40:08.448
and everyone feels like they
have a reason to fight for it.

40:08.448 --> 40:09.908
You mean
our legally binding charter

40:09.908 --> 40:10.909
from a legitimate government.

40:10.909 --> 40:12.452
Your government does not own

40:12.452 --> 40:14.079
every planet in the sky.

40:14.079 --> 40:16.081
But that's not why I'm here.

40:16.081 --> 40:17.624
It's not why I'm here.

40:17.624 --> 40:19.417
I haven't told any of you
the truth, and if I had,

40:19.417 --> 40:21.461
maybe you'd understand
the larger issues at play

40:21.461 --> 40:23.130
and you wouldn't
be wasting time

40:23.130 --> 40:25.924
over this territorial bullshit.

40:25.924 --> 40:28.885
This planet is not
what you think it is.

40:29.594 --> 40:32.222
As soon as the gate opened,
I started being contacted

40:32.222 --> 40:34.141
by a man I knew
who died on Eros.

40:34.141 --> 40:36.810
The Protomolecule was somehow
projecting him into my brain.

40:39.062 --> 40:41.231
You're infected
by the Protomolecule?

40:41.231 --> 40:42.524
No, but I'm in contact
with something.

40:42.524 --> 40:44.734
How?
How does it work?

40:44.734 --> 40:45.944
I don't know
how any of it works.

40:45.944 --> 40:47.654
What does this ghost
want from you?

40:47.654 --> 40:49.865
The Protomolecule was made
to build the Ring gates

40:49.865 --> 40:51.449
and report back
when it was finished.

40:51.449 --> 40:53.785
It wants to reach its creators.

40:53.785 --> 40:55.537
But the things that it was
supposed to report to are gone.

40:55.537 --> 40:56.621
They were killed.

40:56.621 --> 40:57.956
This person in your head

40:57.956 --> 40:59.583
that no one else can see
told you that?

40:59.583 --> 41:01.710
I had a vision when I was
inside the Ring station.

41:01.710 --> 41:04.171
Oh, the ghost didn't tell you,
but the vision did.

41:04.171 --> 41:05.755
I can see why
you didn't tell anyone.

41:05.755 --> 41:07.799
I saw a record
of the old civilization dying,

41:07.799 --> 41:09.885
and I think I saw
what killed them all.

41:09.885 --> 41:12.429
I've had glimpses
during the Ring transits.

41:12.429 --> 41:14.848
Is there any way
to test this information?

41:14.848 --> 41:16.975
Because anyone can claim
to have prophetic visions,

41:16.975 --> 41:18.310
but that doesn't mean that...

41:18.310 --> 41:20.228
Cap's been right
about everything so far.

41:20.228 --> 41:22.814
That thing in his head
is giving him answers.

41:22.814 --> 41:26.151
Or he's just a crazy person
with a few lucky guesses.

41:27.068 --> 41:28.904
I believe
whatever I'm in contact with

41:28.904 --> 41:30.864
is turning on
all the old technology here

41:30.864 --> 41:32.866
to try and understand
what happened to its creators,

41:32.866 --> 41:34.284
and I don't think
it's gonna stop.

41:34.284 --> 41:36.453
I'm not even sure
it can stop.

41:36.453 --> 41:38.330
[Murtry] You're saying
these alien artifacts

41:38.330 --> 41:40.540
are responding to something
that you're doing?

41:40.540 --> 41:42.667
Is there any way we can
use that to control them?

41:42.667 --> 41:44.377
- I don't know.
[Carol] It doesn't matter.

41:44.377 --> 41:47.047
If we leave here, we can't go
to some other system

41:47.047 --> 41:49.549
and find a lithium deposit
like this.

41:49.549 --> 41:51.760
Maybe you did make it worse,

41:51.760 --> 41:54.888
but this place
is our only hope.

41:54.888 --> 41:56.890
We're not giving it up.

41:56.890 --> 41:59.392
[Elvi] What happens
if you leave?

41:59.392 --> 42:02.187
If you're in contact with it,
why don't you just go?

42:02.187 --> 42:04.564
I have no reason to believe
it'll stop once I'm gone.

42:04.564 --> 42:06.816
There is no version of this

42:06.816 --> 42:08.235
where we abandon our charter
and we leave

42:08.235 --> 42:09.444
these squatters and murderers

42:09.444 --> 42:10.737
in possession of this planet.

42:10.737 --> 42:12.197
You're nothing but thieves.

42:12.197 --> 42:15.617
You came here to steal
everything we built!

42:15.617 --> 42:17.369
- It's not happening!
[Holden] Hey! Hey!

42:17.369 --> 42:18.912
Justice to Belters!

42:18.912 --> 42:20.664
Hey!
Hey!

42:20.664 --> 42:23.041
[people yelling]

42:23.041 --> 42:26.044
<i>[country music playing
on headphones]</i>

42:26.044 --> 42:33.051
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:34.719 --> 42:37.180
[computer beeping]

42:37.180 --> 42:44.020
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:55.198 --> 42:57.617
<i>[ominous music]</i>

42:57.617 --> 43:00.245
Oh, my God.

43:00.245 --> 43:07.252
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:36.424 --> 44:39.427
<i>[pensive music]</i>

44:39.427 --> 44:46.434
<i>♪ ♪</i>
